{
  "openapi": "3.0.3",
  "info": {
    "title": "DOXI Sign API",
    "description": "# Getting Started\r\n\r\nWelcome to the **Doxi Sign API**!\r\n\r\nThis guide explains how to authenticate and use key endpoints like creating flows and using templates.  \r\nSwagger: [https://doxi-sign.com/api/swagger](https://doxi-sign.com/api/swagger)\r\n\r\nOpenAPI: [https://doxi-sign.com/api/swagger/v4/swagger.json](https://doxi-sign.com/api/swagger/v4/swagger.json)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Get Access Token (Login)\r\n\r\nAll API requests require a valid access token.\r\n\r\n### Token Endpoint Format\r\n\r\nPOST [https://login.doxi-sign.com/auth/realms/{tenant}/protocol/openid-connect/token](https://login.doxi-sign.com/realms/%7Btenant%7D/protocol/openid-connect/token)\r\n\r\n> Replace `{tenant}` with your actual company name.  \r\nFor example, if your Doxi URL is `https://doxi-sign.com/mycompany`, then:  \r\nPOST [https://login.doxi-sign.com/auth/realms/mycompany/protocol/openid-connect/token](https://login.doxi-sign.com/realms/mycompany/protocol/openid-connect/token) \r\n  \r\n\r\n### Headers\r\n\r\n### Body Parameters\r\n\r\n| Field | Value |\r\n| --- | --- |\r\n| grant_type | password |\r\n| client_id | doxi |\r\n| username | [your@email.com](https://mailto:your@email.com) |\r\n| password | your_password |\r\n| scope | openid |\r\n\r\n> Only `username`, `password`, and `{tenant}` need to be changed.  \r\n`client_id` is always `doxi`. \r\n  \r\n\r\n### Sample Response\r\n\r\n``` json\r\n{\r\n  \"access_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6Ikp...\",\r\n  \"expires_in\": 300,\r\n  \"refresh_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6Ikp...\",\r\n  \"token_type\": \"Bearer\"\r\n}\r\n\r\n ```\r\n\r\n## Required Headers for All API Calls\r\n\r\nEvery request to the Doxi API must include the following headers:\r\n\r\n| Header | Description |\r\n| --- | --- |\r\n| Authorization | `Bearer {access_token}` \u2013 the token obtained from the login step |\r\n| X-Tenant | Your tenant name (e.g., `mycompany`) |\r\n\r\n### Example:\r\n\r\nAuthorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6Ikp...  \r\nX-Tenant: mycompany\r\n\r\n> Your tenant name appears in your Doxi URL:  \r\nIf your portal is `https://doxi-sign.com/mycompany`, your `X-Tenant` is `mycompany`. \r\n  \r\n\r\n## Refresh Token\r\n\r\nWhen your access token expires, you can use the `refresh_token` to obtain a new access token without logging in again.\r\n\r\n### Endpoint\r\n\r\nPOST [https://login.doxi-sign.com/realms/{tenant}/protocol/openid-connect/token](https://login.doxi-sign.com/realms/%7Btenant%7D/protocol/openid-connect/token)\r\n\r\n> Replace `{tenant}` with your actual tenant name (e.g., `mycompany`). \r\n  \r\n\r\n### Headers\r\n\r\n### Body Parameters\r\n\r\n| Field | Value |\r\n| --- | --- |\r\n| grant_type | refresh_token |\r\n| client_id | doxi |\r\n| refresh_token | your_refresh_token |\r\n\r\n### Sample Request\r\n\r\nPOST [https://login.doxi-sign.com/realms/mycompany/protocol/openid-connect/token](https://login.doxi-sign.com/realms/mycompany/protocol/openid-connect/token)  \r\nContent-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded\r\n\r\ngrant_type=refresh_token&  \r\nclient_id=doxi&  \r\nrefresh_token=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6Ikp...\r\n\r\n``` json\r\n{\r\n  \"access_token\": \"new-access-token\",\r\n  \"refresh_token\": \"new-refresh-token\",\r\n  \"expires_in\": 300,\r\n  \"token_type\": \"Bearer\"\r\n}\r\n\r\n ```\r\n\r\nMake sure to update the Authorization header in future API calls with the new access_token\r\n\r\n## Create a New Flow\r\n\r\nThis method creates a signature flow in the Doxi system by uploading a PDF document and defining the process using a JSON payload.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Endpoint\r\n\r\nPOST [https://doxi-sign.com/api/v6/flow](https://doxi-sign.com/api/ex/flow)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Required Headers\r\n\r\nX-Tenant: mycompany  \r\nContent-Type:\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Body Parameters (multipart/form-data)\r\n\r\n| Field | Type | Description |\r\n| --- | --- | --- |\r\n| `File` | File (PDF) | The PDF document to be signed, uploaded as binary stream |\r\n| `CreateFlowJsonRequest` | String (JSON) | The full flow configuration in JSON format |\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Example Request\r\n\r\n**Form Data Fields:**\r\n\r\n- `File`: Upload the actual PDF file (`application/pdf`)\r\n    \r\n- `CreateFlowJsonRequest`: Paste this JSON string:\r\n    \r\n\r\n``` json\r\n{\r\n  \"DocumentFileName\": \"API Example.pdf\",\r\n  \"SenderKey\": {\r\n    \"Key\": \"someUser@SomeDomain.com\",\r\n    \"Type\": 1\r\n  },\r\n  \"Description\": \"API Example test\",\r\n  \"FlowElements\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"SignerKey\": {\r\n        \"Key\": \"someUser@SomeDomain.com\",\r\n        \"Type\": 1\r\n      },\r\n      \"ElementType\": 0,\r\n      \"ElementSubType\": 0,\r\n      \"PageNumber\": 1,\r\n      \"Position\": {\r\n            \"Top\": 440.2,\r\n            \"Left\": 62.0,\r\n            \"Width\": 78.8,\r\n            \"Height\": 37.5\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n  ],\r\n  \"Recipients\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"UserKey\": {\r\n        \"Key\": \"david@doxi.com\",\r\n        \"Type\": 1\r\n      },\r\n      \"Email\": \"david@doxi.com\",\r\n      \"FirstName\": \"David\",\r\n      \"LastName\": \"White\"\r\n    }\r\n  ],\r\n  \"CustomFields\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"Key\": \"SomeInnerSystemIdNumber\",\r\n      \"Value\": \"12345\"\r\n    }\r\n  ],\r\n  \"Users\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"UserKey\": {\r\n        \"Key\": \"someUser@SomeDomain.com\",\r\n        \"Type\": 1\r\n      },\r\n      \"Email\": \"someUser@SomeDomain.com\",\r\n      \"FirstName\": \"Marty\",\r\n      \"LastName\": \"Braun\",\r\n      \"SmsPhoneNumber\": \"0501234567\",\r\n      \"ForceApprovalOnSignature\": false,\r\n      \"PersonalMessage\": \"test 123\"\r\n    }\r\n  ]\r\n}\r\n\r\n ```\r\n\r\nThe CreateFlowJsonRequest must be a string field containing valid JSON, not a nested object.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://content.pstmn.io/3759867e-b364-4eb5-887c-1d12bc9ce1de/Y3JlYXRlIGZsb3cuSlBH\" width=\"452\" height=\"435\">\r\n\r\n### \ud83e\udde0 Field Explanations\r\n\r\n| Field | Description |\r\n| --- | --- |\r\n| `DocumentFileName` | The display name of the PDF document that will appear in the signing process. |\r\n| `SenderKey` | Identifies the user who initiated the signing process. This user receives the final signed document. It includes:  <br>\u2022 `Key`: usually the sender's email  <br>\u2022 `Type`: key type (1 = Email) |\r\n| `Description` | A short message that describes the purpose of the signing flow. Shown to signers in emails and signing screens. |\r\n| `FlowElements` | An array of field definitions (elements) that need to be filled during the signing process. Each element includes:  <br>\u2022 `SignerKey`: who must fill the element  <br>\u2022 `ElementType`: type of field (e.g., signature, checkbox, text)  <br>\u2022 `ElementSubType`: further categorization (optional)  <br>\u2022 `PageNumber`: which page of the document  <br>\u2022 `Position`: coordinates and size (Top, Left, Width, Height) |\r\n| `Recipients` | A list of users who will receive email notifications when the flow is signed or rejected. These users are not signers. |\r\n| `CustomFields` | Optional metadata fields (key-value pairs) attached to the flow. Useful for connecting the flow to internal system IDs or business context. |\r\n| `Users` | List of signers involved in the flow. Each user must have at least an email or phone number.  <br>Additional properties include:  <br>\u2022 `SmsPhoneNumber`: if SMS is used  <br>\u2022 `ForceApprovalOnSignature`: forces confirmation after signature  <br>\u2022 `PersonalMessage`: custom message sent to the signer |\r\n\r\n### Pro Tip: Reverse-Engineer Flow Configuration\r\n\r\nTo determine the exact **element positions**, **field types**, and all required parameters for creating a signing flow via the API, it's recommended to first build a sample process using the **Doxi web interface**.\r\n\r\nOnce the flow is created manually, you can retrieve its full configuration using the following API:\r\n\r\nGET /ex/flow/{signFlowId}\r\n\r\nThis will return all relevant details (including users, elements, field positions, and structure) which you can then reuse to construct the same flow programmatically via the API.",
    "version": "v6.0.0",
    "x-jentic-source-url": "https://apidocs.doxi-sign.com"
  },
  "paths": {
    "/v6/kits/constant": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "Kits"
        ],
        "description": "[V6] Create a new constant kit\n## JSON object description:\n\n* * *\n## createConstantKitRequest:\n\n### Request containing constant kit configuration including kit description, templates, recipients, preliminary text, and external links\n| ***filed*** | ***type*** | ***description*** |\n| ------ | ------ | ------ |\n| Templates | String[] | List of template identifiers included in the kit. |\n| * KitDescription | String(100) | The display name of the kit. |\n| * SenderKey | ***ParticipantKey*** | Id of the Sender |\n| PreliminaryText | String(1000) | Optional introductory text displayed to the kit signer in the lobby screen. |\n| ExternalLinks | ***ExExternalLink[]*** | Optional collection of related external links (for integrations or metadata). |\n| Recipients | ***ExUser[]*** | Optional list of CC recipients associated with the kit. |\n\n* * *\n### ExUser:\n\n| ***filed*** | ***type*** | ***description*** |\n| ------ | ------ | ------ |\n| * UserKey | ***ParticipantKey*** | Id of user |\n| Email | String(77) | Email of user  |\n| FirstName | String(50) | First name of user |\n| LastName | String(50) | Last name of user |\n| SmsPhoneNumber | String(80) | Phone Number of user (if empty, the user will not receive sms) |\n| UserPassword | String Validation: Only letters, numbers, and special characters are allowed. | Password for opening the sign link  |\n| Company | String(80) | Company name of user |\n| Title | String(80) | Title of user |\n| IsDisableAttachment | Nullable\\<Boolean\\> | Disable/Enable add attachments to the flow |\n| IsSuspended | Nullable\\<Boolean\\> | Set status flow to suspended when the signer need to sign |\n| IsNoDecline | Nullable\\<Boolean\\> | Disable/Endable Decline option in flow  |\n| NotificationMailsToSend | ***NotificationMails[]*** | Types of email notifications |\n| MinimumSignatures | Nullable\\<Int32\\> | When the user have optional signature element - Dox validate the minimum signatures in the document |\n| ForceApprovalOnSignature | Nullable\\<Boolean\\> | Force approval on signature |\n| PersonalMessage | String(300) Validation: The field cannot contain script, vbscript, or style tags. | Personal message to the signer |\n| UserPasswordDescription | ***LanguageKey[]*** | Display when the user open the linkfor example: \"Please enter your social security number\"LanguageKey is the message with all supported languages |\n\n* * *\n### LanguageKey:\n\n| ***filed*** | ***type*** | ***description*** |\n| ------ | ------ | ------ |\n| Language | String | language : 'en-US','he-IL' |\n| Value | String | Value of text |\n\n* * *\n### NotificationMails[]:\n\n| ***value*** | ***description*** |\n| ------ | ------ |\n| 0 | All |\n| 1 | None |\n| 2 | SignFlow |\n| 3 | FlowApproved |\n| 4 | FlowDeclined |\n| 5 | FlowStart |\n| 6 | ReminderToSignFlow |\n| 7 | FlowStoppedToSender |\n| 8 | FlowStoppedToSigner |\n| 9 | KitCompleted |\n| 10 | SignKit |\n| 11 | ReminderToSignKit |\n| 12 | KitCreated |\n| 13 | FlowExpired |\n| 14 | FlowCCApproved |\n| 15 | FlowCCDeclined |\n\n* * *\n### ExExternalLink:\n\n| ***filed*** | ***type*** | ***description*** |\n| ------ | ------ | ------ |\n| Description | String(100) |  |\n| Url | String |  |\n\n* * *\n### ParticipantKey:\n\n### Allow to locate Doxi user by:UserEmail=1UserPhone=2\n| ***filed*** | ***type*** | ***description*** |\n| ------ | ------ | ------ |\n| * Key | String | User search value |\n| Type | ***ParticipantKeyType*** | Search type:UserEmail=1,UserPhone=2 |\n\n* * *\n### ParticipantKeyType:\n\n| ***value*** | ***description*** |\n| ------ | ------ |\n| 0 | UserId |\n| 1 | UserEmail |\n| 2 | UserPhone |\n| 3 | UserName |\n| 4 | GroupId |\n",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "X-Tenant",
            "in": "header",
            "description": "Tenant Name",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "default": "{{Tenant}}"
            }
          }
        ],
        "requestBody": {
          "content": {
            "application/json-patch+json": {
              "schema": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ExCreateConstantKitRequest"
