    "/ex/Document/SearchInDocumentBase64": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "Obsolete"
        ],
        "description": "\n## JSON object description:\n\n* * *\n## request:\n\n| ***filed*** | ***type*** | ***description*** |\n| ------ | ------ | ------ |\n| * Base64DocumentFile | String | Base64 encoded document file |\n| * SearchString | String | The string to search for within the document |\n| Pages | String | (optional) Pages to search within the documentComma-separated list of page indices (or ranges) to process. IMPORTANT: the very first page starts at 1 (one).To set a range use the dash -, for example: 1,3-5,7-.To set a range from index to the last page use range like this: 2- |\n| IsCaseSensitive | Nullable\\<Boolean\\> | Flag indicating whether the search should be case-sensitive. By default: false |\n",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "X-Tenant",
            "in": "header",
            "description": "Tenant Name",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "default": "{{Tenant}}"
            }
          }
        ],
